68 INTRODUCTION TO MATHEMATICS 

equation in the form a:^ + (0 Xa:) — 4 = 0. For, 
by the laws stated above, ar^ + (OXa:) — 4 = 
ar^+O— 4=a;2— 4. Hence the equation a:^— 4 
= 0, is merely representative of a particular 
