direction OR is such that the angle ROX is 
equal to the sum of the angles POX and QOX. 

Hence we can conceive the vector OP as 
making the vector OQ rotate through an 
angle POX {i.e. the angle iJOQ= the angle 
POX)y or the vector OQ as making the vector 
OP rotate through the angle QOX (i.e. the 
angle iJOP = the angle QOX). 

